name: HollyFuzz Custom Skate Deck
description: A custom swirly goodness of a skate deck from TheCubb. It is, however, a used skate deck BUT is has been sanded down to a completely smooth finish (just don’t look at the grip tape on the other side!) Could be give given a second lease of life and skated again but HollyFuzz prefers being stuck on someone’s wall, watching life go by and bringing a smile to people’s faces as they walk past. A completely one off and unique piece of artwork so when it’s gone, it’s gone for good. And to be extra nice, shipping is included in the price and should take around 7-14 days from the time of purchase (maybe even quicker….) The HollyFuzz deck came courtesy of friendly skaters and a little time spent alone with some Posca pens. Enjoi xxxx

name: Two By Forty Four Four: Plank
description:
You wouldn’t want to build your fence with these….

	Unlike a normal two by four, if you were hit with this hunk of chunk it would feel slightly fluffier and you’d thank your attacker for using such a high-tech piece of kit.

	Free shipping, only because it’s you who’s buying it, if it was anyone else….

name: CubbStuff Doooooodle
description:
One big fat doodle….

	Posca on painted chipboard, the finsest offcut of old man-made wood you’ll find anywhere! 
This mind numbing piece of Original Art took a fair few hours of autistic style drawing and doodling to complete standing at a whopping 84×60 cm!

	Monster’s, boomboxes, isometry, squiggles, casettes, trumpets and robots, they’re all in there somewhere….

	Completely freehand, no rulers, tippex or extra white paint involved anywhere and with free shipping thrown in, sounds like a pretty swish deal to me.

	Not edible.
